## 2. Core FBs

| FB | Purpose |
|----|---------|
| `FB_IotMqttClient` | MQTT client (connect, publish, subscribe) |
| `FB_IotMqttMessageQueue` | Receive queue for incoming messages |
| `FB_IotMqttMessage` | Single received message (topic + payload) |

## 3. Mandatory Rules

### 3.1 Execute Every Cycle

**Rule:** `_fbMqttClient.Execute(bConnect := TRUE)` MUST be called every PLC cycle.

**Rationale:** The MQTT client is state-driven. Skipping cycles causes connection loss and missed messages.

### 3.2 Subscribe-on-Connect Pattern

**Rule:** Subscribe ONLY when `eConnectionState = ETcIotMqttClientState.Connected AND NOT _bSubscribed`. Set `_bSubscribed := TRUE` after subscribe.

**Rationale:** Subscribing while not connected is silently ignored. The flag prevents duplicate subscriptions every cycle.

```iecst
IF _fbMqttClient.eConnectionState = ETcIotMqttClientState.Connected
   AND NOT _bSubscribed
THEN
    _fbMqttClient.Subscribe(
        sTopic := 'device/+/status',
        eQoS   := TcIotMqttQos.AtLeastOnceDelivery);
    _bSubscribed := TRUE;
END_IF
```

### 3.3 Reconnection Handling

**Rule:** Reset `_bSubscribed := FALSE` when connection state is NOT `Connected`.

**Rationale:** After reconnect the broker has no subscription memory. Without reset, the FB never re-subscribes.

```iecst
IF _fbMqttClient.eConnectionState <> ETcIotMqttClientState.Connected THEN
    _bSubscribed := FALSE;
END_IF
```

### 3.4 Payload Allocation with `__NEW` / `__DELETE`

**Rule:** Always allocate payload dynamically via `__NEW(BYTE, nPayloadSize + 1)`. Always validate `_pPayload <> 0` before use. Always `__DELETE(_pPayload)` after processing.

**Rationale:** MQTT payloads have variable length. Static buffers truncate large payloads. The `+1` ensures null termination for string operations.

```iecst
IF _fbMsgQueue.nQueuedMessages > 0 THEN
    IF _fbMsgQueue.Dequeue(fbMessage := _fbMessage) THEN
        _fbMessage.GetTopic(pTopic := ADR(_sTopic), nTopicSize := SIZEOF(_sTopic));

        _nPayloadSize := _fbMessage.nPayloadSize + 1;
        _pPayload     := __NEW(BYTE, _nPayloadSize);

        IF _pPayload <> 0 THEN
            _fbMessage.GetPayload(
                pPayload            := _pPayload,
                nPayloadSize        := _nPayloadSize,
                bSetNullTermination := TRUE);

            // Parse JSON, route by topic, etc.

            __DELETE(_pPayload);
        END_IF
    END_IF
END_IF
```

### 3.5 Publish Pattern

**Rule:** Use `ADR(sPayload)` + `LEN2(ADR(sPayload))` for string payloads. Use pointer + size for dynamic payloads.

**Rationale:** `LEN2` returns the actual string length (not buffer size). `LEN` would include the null terminator, sending garbage bytes.

```iecst
_fbMqttClient.Publish(
    sTopic       := 'device/cx01/command',
    pPayload     := ADR(sPayload),
    nPayloadSize := LEN2(ADR(sPayload)),
    eQoS         := TcIotMqttQos.AtLeastOnceDelivery,
    bRetain      := FALSE);
```

### 3.6 Topic Routing

**Rule:** Route incoming messages by topic suffix using `FIND()`. Do NOT use string equality — topics may contain dynamic device IDs.

```iecst
IF FIND(_sTopic, '/status') > 0 THEN
    ProcessStatus();
ELSIF FIND(_sTopic, '/result') > 0 THEN
    ProcessResult();
END_IF
```

## 4. QoS Selection

| QoS | Enum | Use case |
|-----|------|----------|
| 0 | `TcIotMqttQos.AtMostOnceDelivery` | Telemetry, status (loss acceptable) |
| 1 | `TcIotMqttQos.AtLeastOnceDelivery` | Commands, control (default choice) |
| 2 | `TcIotMqttQos.ExactlyOnceDelivery` | Financial / safety-critical (slowest) |

**Rule:** Use QoS 1 as default. Only use QoS 0 for high-frequency telemetry. Avoid QoS 2 unless strictly required.

## 5. TLS Configuration

```iecst
_fbMqttClient.stTLS.sCA                := 'c:\TwinCAT\3.1\Target\certs\ca.pem';
_fbMqttClient.stTLS.sCert              := 'c:\TwinCAT\3.1\Target\certs\client.pem';
_fbMqttClient.stTLS.sKeyFile           := 'c:\TwinCAT\3.1\Target\certs\client.key';
_fbMqttClient.stTLS.bNoServerCertCheck := FALSE;
```

**Rule:** Set `bNoServerCertCheck := TRUE` only for local development. Production MUST validate certificates.

## 6. Last Will and Testament

```iecst
_fbMqttClient.sTopicWill   := CONCAT(sTopicPrefix, '/status');
_fbMqttClient.sPayloadWill := '{"online": false}';
_fbMqttClient.eQosWill     := TcIotMqttQos.AtLeastOnceDelivery;
_fbMqttClient.bRetainWill  := TRUE;
```

**Rule:** Set Last Will BEFORE the first `Execute` call. The broker publishes this message when the client disconnects unexpectedly.

## 7. Connection State Reference

| State | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| `Idle` | Not connected, not trying |
| `Connecting` | Connection in progress |
| `Connected` | Connected and ready |
| `Disconnecting` | Disconnect in progress |
| `Error` | Error occurred (check `hrErrorCode`) |

## 8. Wildcard Subscriptions

| Pattern | Meaning | Example |
|---------|---------|---------|
| `+` | Single-level wildcard | `devices/+/status` matches `devices/shelly-001/status` |
| `#` | Multi-level wildcard | `devices/#` matches all sub-topics under `devices/` |

**Rule:** Prefer `+` over `#` to limit message volume. Use `#` only when all sub-topics are relevant.
